# Hand Gesture Mouse Control ğŸ–ï¸ğŸ–±ï¸

This project lets you control your computer mouse using just your "hand gestures"
through your webcam. It uses "OpenCV", "MediaPipe", and "PyAutoGUI" 
to track your hand in real-time and turn gestures into actions like moving the cursor, clicking, and scrolling.

---

## âœ¨ Features

* Real-time "hand tracking" using your webcam.
* Move your mouse by moving your "index finger".
* **Pinch (thumb + index)** to click.
* Optional "scroll mode" using a two-finger gesture.
* Toggle between modes (Mirror / Gesture Overlay / Scroll / Click).
* On-screen UI panel showing FPS, status, and active modes.

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Requirements

Make sure you have Python 3.8+ and install the following dependencies:

```bash
pip install opencv-python mediapipe pyautogui numpy
```

---

## ğŸš€ How to Run

1. Connect a webcam.
2. Open a terminal in the project folder.
3. Run the script:

```bash
python smhand.py
```
A window will open showing your webcam feed with live tracking.
---
## ğŸ® Controls

While the script is running, you can press the following keys:

* "ESC" â†’ Exit
* "M" â†’ Toggle Mirror Mode
* "G" â†’ Toggle Gesture Overlay (landmarks)
* "S" â†’ Toggle Scroll Mode
* "C" â†’ Toggle Click Mode

---

## ğŸ–ï¸ Gestures

* "Move Cursor" â†’ Move your index finger.
* "Click" â†’ Bring thumb and index finger close together (pinch).
* "Scroll (when enabled)** â†’ Hold a â€œpeace âœŒï¸â€ sign (index + middle up), then move your hand up (scroll up) or down (scroll down).

---

## âš ï¸ Notes

* Works best in good lighting.
* Keep your hand in front of the webcam, slightly away for accuracy.
* You may need to adjust sensitivity thresholds in the code for your system.

